no-referrer"></figure></section><p class="article__body-text">最新一期<i>《经济学人》</i>中精选的三篇重要文章被大声朗读。本周：民粹主义共和党人计划如何让<a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/07/13/how-maga-republicans-plan-to-make-donald-trumps-second-term-count">唐纳德·特朗普的第二个任期</a>发挥作用，北约对乌克兰的承诺标志着<a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/07/12/natos-promises-to-ukraine-mark-real-progress">真正的进展</a>，但仍有很多工作要做（10:12），关于<a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/07/13/what-matters-about-the-anthropocene-is-not-when-it-began-but-how-it-might-end">人类主导的人类世地质阶段，</a>重要的不是何时它开始了，但它会如何结束（14:41）。运行时间 20 分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/theeconomisteditorspicks/editors-picks-july-17th-2023" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">请订阅<i>《经济学人》</i>以完全访问印刷版、数字版和音频版： <a href="https://www.economist.com/podcastoffer/">www.economist.com/podcastoffer</a></p><p class="article__body-text">收听： <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/id313848583">Apple 播客</a>| <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/3a5n4DoT1xrV5rgBWBPxnR">Spotify</a> | <a href="https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly9yc3MuYWNhc3QuY29tL3RoZWVjb25vbWlzdGVkaXRvcnNwaWNrcw">谷歌</a>|<a href="https://www.stitcher.com/show/the-economist-editors-highlights-17198">缝合器</a>|<a href="https://tunein.com/podcasts/Politics/Editors-Picks-from-The-Economist-p987585/">调入</a></p>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 16:51:42 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/s3pm25smqaqm7p26jdctcdv2oe4n9kq4</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/podcasts/2023/07/17/how-populist-republicans-plan-to-make-donald-trumps-second-term-count-natos-promises-to-ukraine-and-为什么人类世很重要</item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine at war: Russian uncertainties]]></title><description><![CDATA[<p class="article__body-text"><small><span data-caps="initial">克雷恩号</span>的反击</small>仍在继续，慢慢地夺回阵地并削弱了俄罗斯军队。我们的编辑评估其进展，探讨瓦格纳集团失败的叛变如何影响乌克兰的战斗，并询问弗拉基米尔·普京的政权是否因这一事件而受到致命的破坏。</p><p class="article__body-text">在战场之外，他们考虑七国集团国家最近做出的安全保证是否会给乌克兰赢得战争所需的帮助。</p><p class="article__body-text">与赞尼·明顿·贝多斯、爱德华·卡尔、沙尚克·乔希和阿卡迪·奥斯特洛夫斯基合作。 </p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/e_Nfp4-f1YQ?enablejsapi=1" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">请访问我们的<a href="http://subscriberevents.economist.com/">订户活动页面</a>以查看我们即将举行的活动的时间表。订阅者还可以观看我们之前所有会议的录音。</p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 16:35:14 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/1aem2pdav5flj0vtv1sq8oo60ugqtg2a</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/news/2023/07/17/ukraine-at-war-Russian-uncertainties </item><item><title><![CDATA[Why heatwaves are getting longer, hotter, and more widespread]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230722_PDP501.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><style data-emotion="css 18w36g1">.css-18w36g1{width:100%;font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans);}</style><figcaption class="css-18w36g1 e16qazw92"><style data-emotion="css 11jvxbd">.css-11jvxbd{font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans-smallcaps);font-size:var(--ds-type-scale--1);font-weight:400;font-variant-ligatures:none;line-height:var(--ds-type-leading-lower);text-transform:lowercase;color:var(--ds-color-london-35);}.e16qazw90+.css-11jvxbd{margin-left:0.5rem;}</style><span class="css-11jvxbd e16qazw91">图片：盖蒂图片社</span></figcaption></figure></section><p class="article__body-text">欧洲、美洲和亚洲都在忍受酷热的热浪，气温屡屡<a href="https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2023/07/07/global-temperatures-have-broken-records-three-times-in-a-week" data-tegid="k6947fp8e1t67m82efrj1bbj404kl20u">打破纪录</a>，对健康的影响令人震惊。但最坏的情况还没有到来吗？为什么尽管有战争、通货膨胀和经济衰退的威胁， <a href="https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2023/07/04/can-anything-pop-the-everything-bubble" data-tegid="mbtjrpcot89v52816u19tllav11t64ad">风险资产的</a>弹性仍比投资者预期的要强 (10:10)。欧洲告别了其标志性的<a href="https://www.economist.com/europe/2023/06/21/a-farewell-to-small-cars-the-industrial-icons-that-put-europe-on-wheels" data-tegid="jqkhv4qqi619khpbgnqsb4rohm4sj7ma">小型汽车</a>(16:50)。时长：24分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/theintelligencepodcast/cruel-summer-heatwaves-rage-across-the-world" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">收听： <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-intelligence-from-the-economist/id1449631195">Apple 播客</a>| <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/12zKAMNyS2GNentUzxq9QN">Spotify</a> 